# CODEOWNERS
# https://docs.github.com/articles/about-codeowners
#
# Order: the LAST matching pattern wins for any given path. None of the
# patterns below overlap, so order here is documentation, not enforcement —
# grouped by risk: enforcement mechanism (can silently defeat protection if
# changed unreviewed) > governance/orientation (misdirects, doesn't break
# anything mechanically) > owned content (ordinary maintainership).
#
# Leading slashes anchor a pattern to the repo root — e.g. /tests/ matches
# only the top-level tests/ directory, never skills/<name>/tests/. Don't
# drop the leading slash on a directory pattern without checking this file's
# scope doesn't silently balloon to every skill.

# Tier 1 — enforcement mechanism
/.github/                      @trungfinity
/scripts/validate_skills.py    @trungfinity
/tests/                        @trungfinity
/.pre-commit-config.yaml       @trungfinity
/.gitlint                      @trungfinity
/pyproject.toml                @trungfinity

# Tier 2 — governance & orientation
/AGENTS.md                     @trungfinity
/CONTRIBUTING.md               @trungfinity
/README.md                     @trungfinity
/template/                     @trungfinity
/LICENSE                       @trungfinity

# Tier 3 — owned content
/skills/decision-records/      @trungfinity
